npstatsRulesTable.name: npstatsRulesTable
npstatsRulesTable.description: Statistical information pertaining to network processor rules. Entries in the table are sorted in descending order of number of flows.

npstatsRulesEntry.name: npstatsRulesEntry
npstatsRulesEntry.description: An entry in the network processor statistics rules table. Rows cannot be created or deleted.

npstatsRulesRank.name: npstatsRulesRank
npstatsRulesRank.description: The numerical ranking in the network processor statistics rules table.

npstatsRulesFlows.name: npstatsRulesFlows
npstatsRulesFlows.description: The number of flows that have triggered this filter.

npstatsRulesSuccess.name: npstatsRulesSuccess
npstatsRulesSuccess.description: The number of times this filter has been successfully matched.

npstatsRulesTotalPercent.name: npstatsRulesTotalPercent
npstatsRulesTotalPercent.description: The number of flows for this filter as a percentage of all flows.

npstatsRulesSuccessPer10K.name: npstatsRulesSuccessPer10K
npstatsRulesSuccessPer10K.description: The number of matches for every 10000 flows triggered.

npstatsTiersTable.name: npstatsTiersTable
npstatsTiersTable.description: Statistical information pertaining to network processor tiers.

npstatsTiersEntry.name: npstatsTiersEntry
npstatsTiersEntry.description: An entry in the network processor statistics tiers table. Rows cannot be created or deleted.

npstatsTierNumber.name: npstatsTierNumber
npstatsTierNumber.description: The network processor statistics tier number.

npstatsTiersReceiveMbps.description: The current receive rate in Mbps.

npstatsTiersTransmitMbps.name: npstatsTiersTransmitMbps
npstatsTiersTransmitMbps.description: The current transmit rate in Mbps.

npstatsTiersRxPktsPerSec.name: npstatsTiersRxPktsPerSec

npstatsTiersMaxPktsPerSec.name: npstatsTiersMaxPktsPerSec
npstatsTiersMaxPktsPerSec.description: The maximum receive rate in packets per sec.

npstatsTiersAvgBytesPerPkt.name: npstatsTiersAvgBytesPerPkt
npstatsTiersAvgBytesPerPkt.description: The average packet size in bytes.

npstatsTiersUtilizationPercent.name: npstatsTiersUtilizationPercent
npstatsTiersUtilizationPercent.description: The percent utilization of this tier.

npstatsTiersRatioToNextPer10K.name: npstatsTiersRatioToNextPer10K
npstatsTiersRatioToNextPer10K.description: The ratio of this tier's throughput to the next per 10K (percent * 100).

npstatsTiersMaxReceiveMbps.name: npstatsTiersMaxReceiveMbps
npstatsTiersMaxReceiveMbps.description: The maximum receive rate in Mbps.

npstatsTiersMaxTransmitMbps.name: npstatsTiersMaxTransmitMbps
npstatsTiersMaxTransmitMbps.description: The maximum transmit rate in Mbps.

npstatsTiersMaxUtilizationPercent.name: npstatsTiersMaxUtilizationPercent
npstatsTiersMaxUtilizationPercent.description: The maximum percent utilization of this tier.

npstatsTiersMaxRatioToNextPer10K.name: npstatsTiersMaxRatioToNextPer10K
npstatsTiersMaxRatioToNextPer10K.description: The maximum ratio of this tier's throughput to the next per 10K (percent * 100).

npstatsTiersExtra.name: npstatsTiersExtra
npstatsTiersExtra.description: Additional statistical information pertaining to network processor tiers.

npstatsTier1BypassMbps.name: npstatsTier1BypassMbps
npstatsTier1BypassMbps.description: The current bypass rate in Mbps.

npstatsTier1Balance.description: The load balance among network processors (1000 = exactly balanced, 0 = all to one processor).

npstatsTier1MaxPktsPerSecA.description: The maximum processor A receive rate in packets per second.

npstatsTier1MaxTxPktsPerSec.description: The maximum transmit rate in packets per second.

npstatsTier1MaxVlanTransPktsPerSec.description: The maximum VLAN translation rate in packets per second.

npstatsTier3MaxTxTrustedPktsPerSec.description: The maximum Tier 3 Trusted packets transmit rate in packets per second.

npstatsTier4MaxTxTrustedPktsPerSec.description: The maximum Tier 4 Trusted packets transmit rate in packets per second.

npstatsSslInsp.name: npstatsSslInsp
npstatsSslInsp.description: Sub-tree for all SSL inspection statistics.

npstatsSslInspCurrentSessions.name: npstatsSslInspCurrentSessions
npstatsSslInspCurrentSessions.description: The current number of active SSL sessions.

npstatsSslInspConnectionRate.name: npstatsSslInspConnectionRate
npstatsSslInspConnectionRate.description: The average SSL connection rate in connections per second. This value is not real-time and will lag approximately 2 minutes from actual due to the time interval for calculating the rate.

npstatsSslInspBlockedMaxConns.name: npstatsSslInspBlockedMaxConns
npstatsSslInspBlockedMaxConns.description: The number of blocked SSL sessions due to maximum connection limit.

npstatsSslInspPassedMaxConns.name: npstatsSslInspPassedMaxConns
npstatsSslInspPassedMaxConns.description: The number of passed (not inspected) SSL sessions due to maximum connection limit.

npstatsSslInspTotalBytesIn.name: npstatsSslInspTotalBytesIn
npstatsSslInspTotalBytesIn.description: The number of inspected inbound SSL bytes.

npstatsSslInspTotalBytesOut.name: npstatsSslInspTotalBytesOut
npstatsSslInspTotalBytesOut.description: The number of inspected outbound SSL bytes.

npstatsStackSegmentPorts.name: npstatsStackSegmentPorts

npstatsStackSegmentMaxTransmitMbps.description: Maximum tx rate in Mbps to all customer facing segment ports.

npstatsStackBalance.name: npstatsStackBalance
npstatsStackBalance.description: The load balance percent accross all stack members

npstatsStackMinBalance.name: npstatsStackMinBalance

npstatsStackSegmentRatioToTier1Per10K.name: npstatsStackSegmentRatioToTier1Per10K
npstatsStackSegmentRatioToTier1Per10K.description: The ratio of this tier's throughput to tier 1 per 10K (percent * 100).

npstatsStackSegmentMaxRatioToTier1Per10K.description: The maximum ratio of this tier's throughput to tier 1 per 10K (percent * 100).

npstatsStackPortsMaxRecieveMbps.description: Maximum rx rate in Mbps from all stacking ports.

npstatsStackPortsTransmitMbps.description: Aggregate tx rate in Mbps for all stacking ports.

npstatsStackMaxRxToSegmentTxMbps.description: Maximum return rate in Mbps for traffic coming in on the stacking ports and transmitted to the segment ports
